fetchNextKeyValue

protected boolean fetchNextKeyValue()
Description copied from class: SplitReaderBase
Fetches the next data item of the split being read. If true, use the SplitReaderBase.setCurrentKeyValue(Object, Object) method to set the new current key/value. If false there are no more key/value records to read. See IteratorBasedSplitReader for an implementation of the abstract fetchNextKeyValue() method.

Specified by:
fetchNextKeyValue in class SplitReaderBase<KEY,VALUE>
Returns:
false if reached end of the split, true otherwise.
